## Migration Plan

### Phase 1: Foundation (Weeks 1-2)

**Goals:**
- Implement core Agent base class
- Set up AIVYOrchestrator with routing
- Create database schema
- Implement StateManager (pause/resume)

**Deliverables:**
```typescript
âœ“ Agent base class with 12-factor compliance
âœ“ IntentRouter with LLM-based classification
âœ“ ContextBuilder with priority-based packing
âœ“ StateManager with pause/resume capability
âœ“ Database tables and migrations
âœ“ Unit tests for core components
```

**Migration Steps:**
1. Deploy new database schema alongside existing
2. Create feature flag for AIVY v2
3. Test with internal users only

---

### Phase 2: Teacher Agents (Weeks 3-5)

**Goals:**
- Implement 3 teacher agents
- Migrate existing teacher features
- A/B test with pilot teachers

**Deliverables:**
```typescript
âœ“ CurriculumArchitectAgent (replaces LessonPlanAgent)
âœ“ AssignmentGraderAgent (replaces FeedbackAgent)
âœ“ ContentStudioAgent (replaces WorksheetAgent)
âœ“ API endpoints for teacher agents
âœ“ Integration tests
âœ“ Teacher UI updates
```

**Migration Strategy:**
```typescript
// Feature flag for gradual rollout
if (featureFlags.enableAIVYv2) {
  // Use new agent system
  return await orchestrator.launchAgent("curriculum-architect", ...);
} else {
  // Fallback to old system
  return await legacyLessonPlanAgent.execute(...);
}
```

